  • Method Details

    • changeColor

      public List<BufferedImage> changeColor(List<BufferedImage> original, int r, int g, int b, boolean isSelection)
      this is very handy because this allows me to be able to choose any team color and to paint every image of the units only once this is also used to make the unselected versions of the images
      Parameters:
      original - originally it was used for the units and those have images from all directions, that is why this is a list
      r - the selected pixels will change the red in their rgb value by this amount
      g - the selected pixels will change the green in their rgb value by this amount
      b - the selected pixels will change the blue in their rgb value by this amount
      isSelection - if the returned list is supposed to be a selection that means the gray pixels should be changed too otherwise it is team color change that ignores gray pixels
      Returns:
      the changed version of the original as new images

    • combineImages

      public BufferedImage combineImages(BufferedImage base, BufferedImage upper)
      this is very handy because tiles get their images assigned at initialisation and with this I can put the obsacle images or the road images onto the tile images this is purely for the aestetics (like bridges going over shallow water)
      Parameters:
      base - the base image or the skin
      upper - the image that is printed on the base, or the tattoo
      Returns:
      the base image but where the upper also has a pixel now has the same color as the upper or the hand with a new tattoo
